§ Main result ⦉
<statement type='proposition'>
  ‖ Let $R ∈ 𝗥$. ⦉

  ‖ The set $\Set{-r}{r ∈ R \text{ and } s ∉ R}$ is an
    additive inverse of $R$ in $𝗥$. ⦉
</statement>

§ Notation ⦉
¶ ⦊
  ‖ We denote the additive inverse of $R ∈ 𝗥$ by $-R$. ⦉
